ACEINDEX
-------------------------------

The aceindex.cc script reads in data dumps from AceDB and loads them into a
Xapian database used for searching by the WormBase website.

author: Abigail Cabunoc


INSTALL
-------------------------------

  To install before compiling the indexer:
    C++ libraries:
      http://oligarchy.co.uk/xapian/1.2.4/xapian-core-1.2.4.tar.gz (also needed to run search)
      http://www.hyperrealm.com/libconfig/libconfig-1.4.8.tar.gz

  To install to run the search (not needed for running the indexer):
    C++ library:
      http://oligarchy.co.uk/xapian/1.2.4/xapian-core-1.2.4.tar.gz
    Perl modules:
      Search::Xapian
      Catalyst::Model::Xapian



INDEXING ACEDB
-------------------------------


  1) Compile Indexer (if not compiled already)
      g++ -o aceindex -L/usr/local/lib -l xapian -lconfig++ aceindex.cc

     NOTE:  you may need to do this:
            export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:/usr/local/lib


  2) Dump AceDB
      cd /usr/local/wormbase/acedb/bin
      ./tace ../wormbase

      acedb> @dump_ace_for_search.script


  3) Run Indexer
      ./aceindex settings.conf WSXXX

     NOTE:  remember to set the database version. Also, you may 
            want to look at settings.conf to make sure everything 
            is set properly.
